This article is a letter written by President Barack Obama to President Raul Castro of Cuba, confirming that the United States and Cuba have decided to re-establish diplomatic relations and permanent diplomatic missions in each other's countries on July 20, 2015. The letter emphasizes the intention to develop respectful and cooperative relations between the two countries, in accordance with international law and principles such as the sovereign equality of states, peaceful dispute resolution, respect for territorial integrity, and promotion of human rights. It also mentions that both countries are parties to the Vienna Convention on Diplomatic Relations and the Vienna Convention on Consular Relations, which will apply to their diplomatic and consular relations.